Exxaro Says Richards Bay Export Capacity Limited, May Ship Via Mozambique

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-08-18T05:21:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/exxaro-says-richards-bay-export-capacity-limited-may-ship-via-mozambique.html
Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  said its
capacity to export coal from Richards Bay Coal Terminal on  South
Africa ’s eastern coast will be limited to 2.9 million metric
tons this year.  After an expansion of RBCT, Exxaro should have an export
allocation of 6.3 million tons, it said. As a result, the
company plans to send the remainder of its coal exports “on a
free-on-rail basis, through the lease of export entitlement, or
via Maputo in  Mozambique , it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  